Gunmen on Wednesday kidnapped a retired Chief Pharmacist with Ekiti Ministry of Health, Mr Israel Bamisaye in Orin-Ekiti, Ido/Osi local government areas. It was reliably gathered that Bamisaye was kidnapped by a seven-man gang along his farm located between Ero Dam and the Ekiti State farm settlement in the rustic town. A community source, who doesn’t want his name in print, told The Nation that the former Chief pharmacist was kidnapped around 4pm while working on his farm. The source said that the development has heightened tension and panic in the town. The source said: “The seven gunmen had earlier attacked one man identified as Ojo within the vicinity of the farm where Bamisaye was kidnapped.   Are you ashamed of your national flag?     FEC approves N52.204bn for contract reviews     Tinubu will lead APC to victory in 2023 – Uzodimma   “The man was asked about the whereabouts of the white men working at the farm settlement, but he replied that he didn’t know where they were. “They ordered him to lie face down. They ransacked his car that was parked nearby and took away N4,500 they found inside the vehicle. “They fired a shot and terrified the environment before they later found the victim and whisked him away”. The Police Public Relations Officer, Ekiti Command, DSP Sunday Abutu, could not be reached to confirm the incident. Several calls made to him were neither picked not replied. But the Commander , Ekiti State Amotekun Corps, Brig Gen Joe Akomolafe, confirmed the incident. Akomolafe succinctly said: “We are aware of the kidnapping and my men are really working on it”.